gparted: gparted (GNOME Partition Editor)
gparted:
gparted: GParted is an industrial-strength package for creating, destroying, 
gparted: resizing, moving, checking and copying partitions, and the 
gparted: filesystems on them. This is useful for creating space for new 
gparted: operating systems, reorganizing disk usage, copying data residing on 
gparted: hard disks and mirroring one partition with another (disk imaging).
gparted: 
gparted: GParted uses GNU libparted to detect and manipulate devices and 
gparted: partition tables.
